Package: bayesbiomarkertest
Title: Bayesian Biomarker Testing
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Frank",
           family = "Dondelinger",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "fdondelinger.work@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: This package takes as input drug response summary measurements (such as IC50 or area under the drug-response curve) together with the standard errors of these measurements as well as biomarker measurements, and performs Bayesian inference using a hierarchical linear model to estimate the association between the biomarkers and the drug response.
